== Rice ==

Boil a full #kettle.

When boiling, pour the water into a large #saucepan with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Prep ==

While the rice cooks, halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces) into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @green chilli{1/2}(halved, deseeded and finely chopped) lengthways, deseed, then finely chop.

== Curry ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the onion and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Stir in the @korma curry paste{50%g}, @garam masala{1%tsp}, garlic and half the green chilli (careful, it's hot - add less if you don't like heat). Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @diced chicken breast{260%g}, @tomato passata{1%400g can}, @water for the sauce{100%ml} and @chicken stock paste{1%tsp}. Bring to the boil and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Lower the heat slightly and simmer until thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once thickened, add the @baby spinach{100%g} to the sauce a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Simmer until the sauce has reduced slightly and the chicken is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir through the @mango chutney{40%g} and @butter{20%g}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

== To Serve ==

Fluff up the rice with a #fork, then divide between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chicken curry.

Finish with a sprinkle of the remaining green chilli. Enjoy!

> Step 4 MOD: If you've chosen to get diced chicken breast instead of thigh, cook the recipe in the same way.